        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I played from closed beta until about two months after release.  When it came down to it, DAOC was just boring.  </P><P>There were other problems... Mythic had a really bad habit of nerfing you badly, quickly and without notice.  PvP was a total joke... it was really just a high level gankfest.  The way it was coded, if someone was 4 levels above you, you couldn't land a damn thing on them, while they enjoyed critical hits against you.  1 level 50 could kill an army of level 30s, and probably go AFK during the fight. It was so lame.  The realms, kind of nice at first, quickly became stale.  They are basically carbon copies of them selves.  Every town is pretty much the same.  That goes for players too.  Everyone has a stupid damn cape on.  Everyone has the same graphic textures (just dyed a few different colors).  </P><P>Mythic totally lied about exp gathering, I, like many others, was enticed by the idea that exp would not begathered by endless mob killing, but rather you could gain exp by doing realm quests.  This was only true for the first 20 levels, a monkey with brain damage can level 1-20 in a few days.  After level 20, you are required to mob kill your way for 30 grueling levels... yeaaa fun?  Mythic mislead a lot of people on that one.</P><P>DAOC was a good idea implemented very badly.</P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377</a></P><P></P><P>Edited by - Xuraz on 06/12/2002  07:47:54</font></td>
